1
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:27,875
[ANNOUNCER 3A]
Attention.

2
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:29,791
The train is approaching
the platform.

3
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:33,541
For your safety, please stand
behind the yellow line.

4
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:34,958
You have arrived
at Hyoshi Station.

5
00:00:35,041 --> 00:00:36,875
We've got a game!

6
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:38,833
Settle down, Gion.

7
00:00:38,916 --> 00:00:39,875
[IWASHIMIZU grunts]

8
00:00:39,958 --> 00:00:41,958
[GION]
But I'm really excited! Sir!

9
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:44,625
[HACHIOJI] Yeah, I know.
Just keep it together.

10
00:00:56,958 --> 00:00:58,875
Huh?

11
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:03,125
We gotta big game today,
tree trunk. Smile.

12
00:01:03,208 --> 00:01:06,041
Big? It's just practice.

13
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:07,375
Hm?

14
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:47,833
[GION] So this is Keijo High!
They're goin' down!

15
00:02:47,916 --> 00:02:48,958
[EBUMI]
Relax!

16
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:50,416
I already told you
you're not gonna see

17
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:51,958
the field today, tiny mite.

18
00:02:52,041 --> 00:02:53,208
Shut up!

19
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:55,541
Don't fight, you guys,
you're on the same team.

20
00:02:55,625 --> 00:02:58,375
Gion. Here, carry this.

21
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:01,791
[GION] You can lug your own
crap around, jack hole!

22
00:03:01,875 --> 00:03:04,250
[KAMO] I just wanted
you to feel involved.

23
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:09,750
It looks like we got here
with some time to spare.

24
00:03:09,833 --> 00:03:12,750
[TAIRA]
Sekizan!

25
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:14,041
[gasps]

26
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:18,291
Wow. You've... changed!

27
00:03:18,375 --> 00:03:20,166
Wrong guy.

28
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:23,791
Yeah. I'm right here, Taira.

29
00:03:23,875 --> 00:03:26,541
I know, I'm just jokin' around!

30
00:03:26,625 --> 00:03:29,791
Aw, come on.
Can't you say, "hi"?

31
00:03:29,875 --> 00:03:31,208
[SEKIZAN]
Hi.

32
00:03:31,291 --> 00:03:32,250
[TAIRA]
What's up?

33
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:34,333
Aren't you glad
to see me, Sekizan?

34
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:35,708
[SEKIZAN]
No.

35
00:03:36,833 --> 00:03:38,250
That guy is weird.

36
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:41,250
He's Keijo's vice-captain, too.

37
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:42,625
After you guys suit up,

38
00:03:42,708 --> 00:03:44,583
meet us on the
south field, okay?

39
00:03:44,666 --> 00:03:47,708
Make it quick! 'Cause
we're ready to rock!

40
00:03:47,791 --> 00:03:50,583
[TAIRA laughs]

41
00:03:50,666 --> 00:03:52,000
[door slams]

42
00:03:52,958 --> 00:03:55,500
That guy sucks. He's the worst.

43
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:58,583
Yep! The lunatic
hasn't changed a bit.

44
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:02,750
All right, guys.

45
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:05,291
Here's today's starting lineup.

46
00:04:11,458 --> 00:04:13,791
[TAIRA]
Mm... Huh?

47
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:15,583
Game on!

48
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:17,375
Okay.

49
00:04:22,125 --> 00:04:26,000
We're here. You ready to play?

50
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:30,500
Absolutely.

51
00:04:32,083 --> 00:04:34,083
[TAIRA]
Damn right we are.

52
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:39,291
For two years,
I've waited for this day.

53
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:46,500
Our time has
finally come, Sekizan.

54
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:48,291
You and me.

55
00:04:53,208 --> 00:04:56,916
That's enough talking
for one day. Let's play!

56
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:15,833
[footsteps]

57
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,166
[MIYUKI]
You starting?

58
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:19,750
[IWASHIMIZU]
Yep.

59
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,708
Uh... Is your shoulder--?

60
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:32,458
It's good as new.

61
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:36,666
[MIYUKI chuckles]

62
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,541
How come I don't get to play?

63
00:05:39,625 --> 00:05:41,083
This sucks!

64
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:44,708
If freakin' tree trunk is
out there, I should be, too!

65
00:05:44,791 --> 00:05:47,041
Put me in, Captain!

66
00:05:47,125 --> 00:05:48,875
[MIYUKI]
Hey! You!

67
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:51,750
[IWASHIMIZU]
No! Miyuki, wait!

68
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,750
Who's a tree trunk?

69
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,916
Huh?!

70
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,583
You better take that back.

71
00:05:57,666 --> 00:06:00,541
Or we've got a problem.

72
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:02,625
[IWASHIMIZU]
Miyuki!

73
00:06:02,708 --> 00:06:05,291
Iwashi's my friend and he's
a hell of a player, too.

74
00:06:05,375 --> 00:06:06,875
So apologize now.

75
00:06:06,958 --> 00:06:09,416
I-It's okay, just let it go.

76
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,916
[MIYUKI]
Once you see him play,

77
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,791
you'll understand.

78
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:37,291
[EBUMI, GION]
This sucks.

79
00:06:37,375 --> 00:06:39,250
Well, the air is
thick with irony.

80
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,958
Don't ya think?

81
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,000
[UMENO]
By the way, Gion.

82
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:46,416
Have you studied up
on the rules yet?

83
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:47,791
Yeah, I have!

84
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:49,125
You can't throw
the ball forward,

85
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:50,916
and you try not to drop it.

86
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,041
I should smack you in the face.

87
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:57,166
[whistle blows]

88
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:59,458
[REF 3A]
Keijo will now kick off!

89
00:07:07,583 --> 00:07:08,625
[grunts]

90
00:07:08,708 --> 00:07:10,000
[groans]

91
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:12,166
[whistle blows]

92
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:14,833
[REF 3A]
Knock-on by Jinko!

93
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:16,708
That's a forward ball drop!

94
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:19,583
You're right.
Now they have a scrum.

95
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:25,666
[TAIRA] You better
get to know me, Jinko!

96
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:28,958
The name is Taira and I'm
the best hooker in the game!

97
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:30,666
Bow down, losers!

98
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,875
Yeah. Whatever you say.

99
00:07:34,875 --> 00:07:37,708
All right, let's
get to work, guys.

100
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:41,125
Iwashimizu, push as
hard as ya can, okay?

101
00:07:41,208 --> 00:07:42,875
Right.

102
00:07:42,958 --> 00:07:45,125
[REF 3A]
Crouch!

103
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:46,625
Bind!

104
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:48,541
[REF 3A]
Set!

105
00:07:48,625 --> 00:07:53,125
[KEIJO TEAM, JINKO TEAM yelling]

106
00:07:53,208 --> 00:07:56,875
[HACHIOJI] I've never felt this
kinda push from a team before.

107
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:58,208
[KAMO]
Ball's out!

108
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:01,875
I don't like being shown up
by another freshman.

109
00:08:01,958 --> 00:08:03,833
It's time to get serious.

110
00:08:09,791 --> 00:08:11,708
[OHARANO]
Which way will he go?

111
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,458
[OHARANO]
No way! Straight through me?

112
00:08:16,541 --> 00:08:18,458
[BOTH grunting]

113
00:08:18,541 --> 00:08:22,083
Hey, forwards! Get back!

114
00:08:22,166 --> 00:08:23,375
[KIBI]
Got it!

115
00:08:25,125 --> 00:08:28,125
Kibi! Way to tackle!

116
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:29,291
[sighs]

117
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:31,500
That was close.

118
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:32,500
Hey.

119
00:08:32,583 --> 00:08:35,041
So is the Keijo
team really good?

120
00:08:35,125 --> 00:08:37,625
What? Well...

121
00:08:37,708 --> 00:08:41,791
I suppose you wouldn't know
any better, would you?

122
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:43,333
They're real good. They do well

123
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:46,333
in the Kanagawa Prefecture
tournament every time.

124
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:49,375
Last year they gave the reigning
champs a run for their money.

125
00:08:49,458 --> 00:08:52,416
They're talented, tough,
and experienced, too.

126
00:08:54,208 --> 00:08:55,458
[KAMO]
Iwashi!

127
00:08:56,791 --> 00:08:58,333
[IWASHIMIZU]
I need to make a pass.

128
00:09:00,708 --> 00:09:01,458
[whistle blows]

129
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,166
[REF 3A]
Knock-on by Jinko!

130
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:13,500
You're moving too slow.
Get it in gear.

131
00:09:15,166 --> 00:09:17,750
Yeah. I'm sorry, sir.

132
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:24,625
[REF 3A]
Set!

133
00:09:24,708 --> 00:09:30,541
[KEIJO TEAM, JINKO TEAM yelling]

134
00:09:33,958 --> 00:09:36,250
Push 'em way harder
next time, okay?

135
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:37,875
Yeah. Will do!

136
00:09:37,958 --> 00:09:40,666
Jinko's number 5 sucks big time!

137
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:41,833
Target him!

138
00:09:45,708 --> 00:09:47,458
What's the deal, short stuff?

139
00:09:47,541 --> 00:09:49,250
What's wrong with
the jolly lame giant?

140
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:51,416
Don't call me that!

141
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:57,208
[EBUMI]
That guy's totally useless.

142
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:01,250
[MIYUKI]
You better take that back.

143
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:03,291
Or we've got a problem.

144
00:10:03,375 --> 00:10:06,458
[GION growls]

145
00:10:06,541 --> 00:10:07,666
[UMENO] They've been
putting the pressure on

146
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,375
for ten minutes now.

147
00:10:09,458 --> 00:10:11,791
We've got to get the
momentum back fast.

148
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:14,375
That guy? Number 10!

149
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:16,541
He is totally owning us!

150
00:10:22,625 --> 00:10:24,708
[SEKIZAN]
Stop him, Iwashi!

151
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:30,041
Come on now, Iwashi! Bring it!

152
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,791
[whistle blows]

153
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:14,250
[REF 3A]
Try!

154
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:25,000
[MIYUKI]
What the hell?

155
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:30,333
Is this some kind of a joke?

156
00:11:39,541 --> 00:11:42,000
If you won't even
give it your best effort,

157
00:11:42,083 --> 00:11:44,666
you don't even deserve
to play on my field.

158
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:50,250
You're just a useless waste.

159
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:53,708
[MIYUKI]
A loser.

160
00:11:56,375 --> 00:11:58,041
[whistle blows]

161
00:12:00,291 --> 00:12:01,833
[GION]
What is he doing?!

162
00:12:01,916 --> 00:12:04,916
Somebody put me in the game!
Gimme that ball and I'll cram it

163
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,041
down their freakin' throats!

164
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:07,416
You idiot!

165
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,000
You can't play his position,
you're way too small!

166
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:10,000
So?

167
00:12:10,083 --> 00:12:12,625
Just get me off
this stupid bench!

168
00:12:12,708 --> 00:12:13,666
Shut your mouth!

169
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:16,291
And stop acting
like a little child!

170
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:19,125
Put me in.

171
00:12:26,875 --> 00:12:28,666
Sorry. No.

172
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:31,416
Just do what you can
from the sidelines.

173
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:36,416
[GION] I wanna play so bad,
and I'm sidelined.

174
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:38,666
But he gets to play...

175
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,541
...and he doesn't even try.

176
00:12:40,625 --> 00:12:42,791
[yelps]

177
00:12:42,875 --> 00:12:45,375
Hey, tree trunk!

178
00:12:45,458 --> 00:12:47,291
[gasps]

179
00:12:47,375 --> 00:12:50,458
Don't just stand there--hit 'im!

180
00:12:50,541 --> 00:12:52,333
That's our ball he's got!

181
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:54,958
Are you going to let
him take it from you?

182
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:12,500
[MIYUKI]
Oh, yeah!

183
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:13,916
Let's go!

184
00:13:30,625 --> 00:13:32,083
[gasps]

185
00:13:33,625 --> 00:13:43,083
[panting]

186
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:51,000
That's our ball.

187
00:13:51,083 --> 00:13:51,833
[whistle blows]

188
00:13:51,916 --> 00:13:53,833
[REF 3A]
Knock-on by Keijo!

189
00:13:58,125 --> 00:14:00,000
[IWASHIMIZU]

190
00:14:00,083 --> 00:14:03,083
Glad to see you're finally
back in the game, Iwashi.

191
00:14:06,708 --> 00:14:08,250
Thanks.

192
00:14:18,041 --> 00:14:22,708
[KEIJO TEAM, JINKO TEAM
grunting, yelling]

193
00:14:22,791 --> 00:14:24,083
We got the ball now!

194
00:14:24,166 --> 00:14:25,916
Go get 'em, guys!

195
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:33,750
Come on! Now!

196
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:40,708
Well, look who it is!

197
00:14:40,791 --> 00:14:48,000
You're goin' down, big guy!

198
00:14:48,083 --> 00:14:49,333
Huh?

199
00:14:54,083 --> 00:14:55,000
[IWASHIMIZU grunts]

200
00:14:55,083 --> 00:14:56,625
[whistle blows]

201
00:14:56,708 --> 00:14:58,958
Penalty against Keijo!

202
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:02,666
We call that "over the top."

203
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:05,083
Ya can't fall over the ball.

204
00:15:11,083 --> 00:15:12,041
[whistle blows]

205
00:15:12,125 --> 00:15:13,291
All right.

206
00:15:13,375 --> 00:15:15,041
So the ball's just been
kicked out of bounds!

207
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:17,541
Tell me what happens next.

208
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:18,750
Let's see.

209
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:20,875
Well, if the ball's been
kicked out of play,

210
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:22,416
that's when we
jump for the ball.

211
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:24,833
That's right! It's
called a line out.

212
00:15:24,916 --> 00:15:26,791
Excellent work, Gion.

213
00:15:26,875 --> 00:15:27,625
Cut it out!

214
00:15:27,708 --> 00:15:29,458
[chuckles]

215
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:32,416
[GION]
Hold on.

216
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,666
So you throw the ball
in between two lines.

217
00:15:34,750 --> 00:15:36,791
Your team's and your opponents.

218
00:15:36,875 --> 00:15:39,250
But why can't we just throw
it to one of our own guys.

219
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:41,416
I mean, they fouled us, right?

220
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:44,500
Because, Gion, rugby is
a gentleman's sport.

221
00:15:44,583 --> 00:15:47,166
Even after a foul, both team's
are given an opportunity

222
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:49,208
to regain possession
of the ball.

223
00:15:57,083 --> 00:16:00,375
[OCHIAI] You're not snatchin'
the rock from me, big man.

224
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:04,541
Oh! Too high!

225
00:16:04,625 --> 00:16:06,583
Don't worry. It's all mine!

226
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:08,833
[gasps]

227
00:16:18,458 --> 00:16:20,375
[OCHIAI]
Whoa! One-handed.

228
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:24,333
Wow.

229
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:26,791
"Wow's" right.

230
00:16:26,875 --> 00:16:28,833
'Course it helps that
he's so freakin' massive.

231
00:16:28,916 --> 00:16:30,208
Matsuo?

232
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:36,000
[MATSUO] After all, rugby
is a very physical sport.

233
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,916
[GION gasps]

234
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,833
[HACHIOJI]
Hisakawa's comin' out!

235
00:16:42,166 --> 00:16:43,833
All right!

236
00:16:43,916 --> 00:16:46,708
Crap! They just
turned the ball over!

237
00:16:54,458 --> 00:16:56,333
You're all mine!

238
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,625
Hirota! Nice job!

239
00:17:00,708 --> 00:17:02,958
[BOTH grunting]

240
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:03,541
[TAIRA grunts]

241
00:17:03,625 --> 00:17:05,125
[gasps]

242
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:08,833
Nice pass!

243
00:17:08,916 --> 00:17:10,416
[yelps]

244
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,166
This sucks.

245
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:16,291
Keijo is a prestige
private school

246
00:17:16,375 --> 00:17:18,541
and they have more
resources, too.

247
00:17:18,625 --> 00:17:20,333
Which means their
athletes are stronger

248
00:17:20,416 --> 00:17:22,375
and have better
training over all.

249
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:25,583
In terms of physicality,
we're out matched.

250
00:17:25,666 --> 00:17:27,000
They're just too good.

251
00:17:27,083 --> 00:17:29,166
There's no way we can compete.

252
00:17:31,416 --> 00:17:34,458
[MATSUO]
Maybe not.

253
00:17:34,541 --> 00:17:37,166
But physical ability
isn't everything.

254
00:17:37,250 --> 00:17:37,958
Trust me.

255
00:17:38,041 --> 00:17:42,000
[SEKIZAN yelling]

256
00:17:47,416 --> 00:17:49,875
[yelps]

257
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:51,458
[SEKIZAN grunts]

258
00:17:51,541 --> 00:17:54,333
[MATSUO] Do you know what
matters most in rugby?

259
00:17:54,416 --> 00:17:56,500
Overcoming your fears.

260
00:17:56,583 --> 00:18:00,375
And never turning
away from a fight.

261
00:18:00,458 --> 00:18:02,333
No matter what.

262
00:18:05,791 --> 00:18:14,875
[TAIRA, SEKIZAN panting]

263
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,000
I love those eyes.

264
00:18:22,083 --> 00:18:24,666
In two years,
they haven't changed.

265
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:28,625
It's true. I fell for
those eyes, Sekizan!

266
00:18:31,916 --> 00:18:36,708
It's my first game with Keijo.
I am so pumped up!

267
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:39,500
Captain! How's the
Jinko Team this year?

268
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:42,250
Are they strong?

269
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:44,083
No, they're weak.

270
00:18:44,166 --> 00:18:47,083
If I had my way, we'd play
a much stronger opponent.

271
00:18:47,166 --> 00:18:48,541
But no one else was available.

272
00:18:48,625 --> 00:18:50,416
[JINKO CAPTAIN 3A]
Are you guys ready to play?

273
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,458
[BOTH gasp]

274
00:18:51,541 --> 00:18:53,541
[JINKO TEAM]
Yes, sir!

275
00:18:53,625 --> 00:18:55,750
[KEIJO CAPTAIN 3A] I'm
surprised you actually showed.

276
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,375
We don't back down
from a challenge,

277
00:18:57,458 --> 00:19:01,000
you know that. Plus, it's good
practice for the new guys.

278
00:19:14,083 --> 00:19:17,750
[whistle blowing]

279
00:19:22,666 --> 00:19:24,250
[JINKO PLAYER 3A]
Man, those private school kids

280
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:25,791
sure are tough!

281
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:27,750
Hey, if it hadn't been
raining like this,

282
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:30,708
we could've kept those guys
under 100 points for sure.

283
00:19:30,791 --> 00:19:33,166
Look. They even have
team showers on site!

284
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:35,666
[JINKO PLAYER 3A]
Whoa. Awesome!

285
00:19:35,750 --> 00:19:38,583
[growls]

286
00:19:38,666 --> 00:19:40,916
[TAIRA yells]
Those losers!

287
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,041
What the hell is
wrong with them?

288
00:19:43,125 --> 00:19:45,041
Hey, just take it easy, Taira.

289
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:47,041
I wont take it easy, okay?

290
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:50,500
Their losing ways'll rub off
on us if we're not careful.

291
00:19:53,875 --> 00:19:55,500
[KEIJO CAPTAIN 3A] I knew we
were gonna kick their butts,

292
00:19:55,583 --> 00:19:57,416
but not by that much.

293
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,625
[ALL gasp]

294
00:19:58,708 --> 00:20:01,125
[SEKIZAN grunts]

295
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:03,625
[SEKIZAN pants]

296
00:20:03,708 --> 00:20:07,708
[panting]

297
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:09,666
[SEKIZAN grunts]

298
00:20:16,291 --> 00:20:18,375
The game's been
over for an hour.

299
00:20:18,458 --> 00:20:20,791
And he's still out there
giving it his all.

300
00:20:31,166 --> 00:20:33,166
What's your name? Tell me.

301
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:43,583
Sekizan Takuya.

302
00:20:52,875 --> 00:20:55,333
[TAIRA] It never mattered
how badly you lost.

303
00:20:55,416 --> 00:20:57,250
You always kept your head up.

304
00:20:57,333 --> 00:20:59,875
You always stayed strong.

305
00:20:59,958 --> 00:21:02,500
[SEKIZAN yells]

306
00:21:02,583 --> 00:21:05,166
But when you look at me
like that, Sekizan...

307
00:21:05,250 --> 00:21:08,166
...every part of me
wants to crush you!

308
00:21:13,583 --> 00:21:14,750
You know, it's funny.

309
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:18,208
I started playin' rugby
in high school, too.

310
00:21:18,291 --> 00:21:21,708
And I thought I trained
as hard as Taku.

311
00:21:21,791 --> 00:21:24,083
But I was just fooling myself.

312
00:21:29,875 --> 00:21:32,125
[MATSUO]
He was the best.

313
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:34,625
And he was the only one
who could really compete.

314
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:37,833
[MATSUO]
But...

315
00:21:39,083 --> 00:21:42,166
[MATSUO]
No one can do it alone.

316
00:21:42,250 --> 00:21:45,875
Unless all 15 guys on
the field want to win,

317
00:21:45,958 --> 00:21:47,875
you're not playin' rugby.

318
00:21:47,958 --> 00:21:51,208
I don't know about you,
but I hate to lose.

319
00:21:51,291 --> 00:21:53,625
I wanna play to compete.

320
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:57,291
To win.

321
00:21:57,375 --> 00:21:59,833
And I want Taku to get us there.

322
00:22:04,708 --> 00:22:06,833
[OHARANO sighs]

323
00:22:06,916 --> 00:22:10,083
If we wanna win, we need
to make some changes.

324
00:23:43,083 --> 00:23:45,750
[GION] Next time:
"What Should I Do?"

